On June 13, 2016, the President signed into law several bills that designate various United States Postal Service facilities as memorials. The bills include:

1. H.R. 136 - Designates the facility at 1103 USPS Building 1103 in Camp Pendleton, California, as the Camp Pendleton Medal of Honor Post Office.
2. H.R. 433 - Designates the facility at 523 East Railroad Street in Knox, Pennsylvania, as the Specialist Ross A. McGinnis Memorial Post Office.
3. H.R. 1132 - Designates the facility at 1048 West Robinhood Drive in Stockton, California, as the W. Ronald Coale Memorial Post Office Building.
4. H.R. 2458 - Designates the facility at 5351 Lapalco Boulevard in Marrero, Louisiana, as the Lionel R. Collins, Sr. Post Office Building.
5. H.R. 2928 - Designates the facility at 201 B Street in Perryville, Arkansas, as the Harold George Bennett Post Office.
6. H.R. 3082 - Designates the facility at 5919 Chef Menteur Highway in New Orleans, Louisiana, as the Daryle Holloway Post Office Building.
7. H.R. 3274 - Designates the facility at 4567 Rockbridge Road in Pine Lake, Georgia, as the Francis Manuel Ortega Post Office.
8. H.R. 3601 - Designates the facility at 7715 Post Road, North Kingstown, Rhode Island, as the Melvoid J. Benson Post Office Building.
9. H.R. 3735 - Designates the facility at 200 Town Run Lane in Winston Salem, North Carolina, as the Maya Angelou Memorial Post Office.
10. H.R. 3866 - Designates the facility at 1265 Hurffville Road in Deptford Township, New Jersey, as the First Lieutenant Salvatore S. Corma II Post Office Building.
11. H.R. 4046 - Designates the facility at 220 East Oak Street, Glenwood City, Wisconsin, as the Second Lt. Ellen Ainsworth Memorial Post Office.
12. H.R. 4605 - Designates the facility at 615 6th Avenue SE in Cedar Rapids, Iowa as the Sgt. 1st Class Terryl L. Pasker Post Office Building.